{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 20 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:1",
      "text": "Wine is an intemperate thing, and strong drink full of violence: but every fool is entangled with them.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:2",
      "text": "The threat of a king differs not from the rage of a lion; and he that provokes him sins against his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:3",
      "text": "It is a glory to a man to turn aside from railing; but every fool is entangled with such matters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:4",
      "text": "A sluggard when reproached is not ashamed: so also he who borrows corn in harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:5",
      "text": "Counsel in a man’s heart is deep water; but a prudent man will draw it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:6",
      "text": "A man is valuable, and a merciful man precious: but it is hard to find a faithful man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:7",
      "text": "He that walks blameless in justice, shall leave his children blessed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:8",
      "text": "Whenever a righteous king sits on the throne, no evil thing can stand before his presence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:9",
      "text": "Who will boast that he has a pure heart? or who will boldly say that he is pure from sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:10",
      "text": "A large and small weight, and divers measures, are even both of them unclean before the Lord; and so is he that makes them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:11",
      "text": "A youth when in company with a godly man, will be restrained in his devices, and then his way will be straight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:12",
      "text": "The ear hears, and the eye sees: even both of them are the Lord’s work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:13",
      "text": "Love not to speak ill, lest thou be cut off: open thine eyes, and be filled with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:14",
      "text": "The lamp of him that reviles father or mother shall be put out, and his eyeballs shall see darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:21",
      "text": "A portion hastily gotten at first shall not be blessed in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:22",
      "text": "Say not, I will avenge myself on my enemy; but wait on the Lord, that he may help thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:23",
      "text": "A double weight is an abomination to the Lord; and a deceitful balance is not good in his sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:24",
      "text": "A man’s goings are directed of the Lord: how then can a mortal understand his ways?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:25",
      "text": "It is a snare to a man hastily to consecrate some of his own property: for in that case repentance comes after vowing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:26",
      "text": "A wise king utterly crushes the ungodly, and will bring a wheel upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:27",
      "text": "The spirit of man is a light of the Lord, who searches the inmost parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:28",
      "text": "Mercy and truth are a guard to a king, and will surround his throne with righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:29",
      "text": "Wisdom is an ornament to young men; and grey hairs are the glory of old men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.20.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:30",
      "text": "Bruises and contusions befall bad men; and plagues shall come in the inward parts of their belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
